<TITLE> Abahani-Arambagh match shifted to Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 22 (bdnews24.com) Dhaka Abahani's B. League home match against Arambagh KS was shifted to Monday considering the continuous heavy monsoon rainfall Sunday. "We visited the venue and found it 'unplayable' after the Saturday match coupled with the incessant rainfall, and we decided to shift the match to Monday," said B. League manager Abu Nayeem Shohag Sunday. He added that the remaining fixture of B. League would remain unchanged and the 21st round of the first-ever professional football league would commence on Tuesday accordingly with Farashganj SC taking on visitors Chittagong Abahani Limited. Dhaka Abahani are jointly leading the 11-team point table along with arch rivals Dhaka Mohammedan SC, both sides having 38 points. Abahani, however, have played a match less than Mohammedan's 18. 
